comment_text: When asking for growth life does not give you discomfort, it gives you the awareness of your discomfort. It doesn’t demand sacrifice, it makes you aware of what’s holding you back. When you aim for greatness make sure you understand what it looks like to you otherwise you’ll get stuck in a loop of burnout waiting for the feeling to come. You can handle responsibility with ease or you can be frantic about it. We don’t need to keep up this negative narrative around growth and success. There is no price to pay only a refund for what held you back in the first place.

comment_text:
No, this isn’t what I asked for :melting_face: 
Success isn’t built on struggle and sacrifice alone. Growth isn’t just about enduring discomfort… it’s about learning, evolving, and finding alignment with what truly matters. The idea that ambition must come at the cost of peace or free time feels…outdated. Success isn’t just about pushing harder it’s also about working smarter, prioritizing well-being, and creating a life that feels fulfilling, not just productive. We can embrace ambition without burning ourselves out. We can grow without suffering. We can build the lives we want while still making space for joy, rest, and balance.
Release the shackles of hustle culture, and LIVE.
